IMPORTANT: Governor Tim Walz signed an executive order requiring Minnesotans to wear a face covering in all public indoor spaces and indoor businesses beginning Saturday, July 25, 2020 to help prevent the spread of COVID-19.

Accordingly, when students do return to WLA, face coverings will be required for all students (in grades K-8), all staff and anyone present at WLA.

The Minnesota Department of Education (MDE) is also requiring all kindergarteners, even those under the age of five, to wear a face covering.

If you have any questions, please contact our main office! 651.570.2100 or info@wlamn.org. #InThisTogether

post_text:
What brightens up a day? Seeing student artwork! ‚ù§Ô∏èüß°üíõüíöüíôüíú#CoreKnowledge

Scientist Week:
Students learned about how scientists play an important role in our understanding of how the world works. Our students learned about the range of concepts studied in science by briefly reading about two scientists, Issac Newton and Jane Goodall. The K-2 kiddos learned about diffusion art, 3-5 students designed a never before seen robot, and the 6-8 students created a rocket with unique features when planning a safe trip to Mars.

Color Wheel:
After learning about scientists, it only seemed fitting to learn about theory. This week focused on color theory and the mixing of colors based upon the color wheel diagram. WLA kiddos found a unique way to visually represent the color wheel.

Consider this: Just as we want our students to be leaders and live virtuous lives, the WLA community must model those same ideals. One way we do this is by volunteering to be a board member and/or voting for new members on the Board of Directors.

This year, 3 open seats are up for election (Term June 2020 - June 2023): One parent, one teacher, one community member

For more information, check out the election 2020 letter and our school site! http://www.wlamn.org/about-wla/board/

Thank you!

Does your student's last name start with a U-Z?! Then TODAY is your day to pick up their materials at WLA between 8AM-6PM. Please stay in your vehicles!!

In an effort to comply with social distancing, please follow the pick-up guidelines by last name:

A-G - Tuesday, March 24th
H-M - Wednesday, March 25th
N-T - Thursday, March 26th
U-Z - Friday, March 27th

Please pull into the handicap spaces in front of the main doors between 8am - 6pm to claim your students‚Äô things.

Visitors will be asked to remain in their vehicles and call 651-571-2100. A staff member will bring your items to you.

WLA is asking no visitors enter the building.

WLA is working on an intercom system, for those who don't have access to a cell phone to call from outside the building. In the meantime please call ahead with a window of your arrival.

post_text:
We asked some 5th grade students why our school is special. Here are the powerful responses:

"More diverse."
"Teachers teach us how to be responsible and kind to each other."
"If you don't understand something, teachers are always willing to help."
"We learn more than what we are supposed to for our grade level."
"We learn how to be a good sport during P.E."
"Teachers are more fair to the students."
"The consequence are based on what you did."
"Basically, everyone is happy. There is less bullying. Less fights."
"We can learn from other students on how to act because everyone is kind."

Please help keep these powerful responses coming by supporting our school. Every dollar donated goes directly towards our students. As you may be aware, we receive significantly less funding per child than traditional public schools due to not being able to collect property taxes.

To donate, click on the link or bring cash/check to WLA main office. https://www.givemn.org/organization/Wlamn

Thank you for all your support!

We're excited to announce that we have raised $2,815.00 so far from our Give to the Max fundraiser! The fundraiser will end on Saturday, November 30th. We hope this amount of time will allow for us to reach our goal of $10,000.00! It's a big goal, but leaders do extraordinary things!

Thank you for taking the time to support our students! Our WLA family ROCKS!!

Have a great weekend!

post_text:
Hello Families! We realize there is clarity needed in regards to appropriate clothing for celebrating Unity Day tomorrow! We hope this clarifies all inquires. If not, write a comment on this post. üòä

"Together against bullying. UNITED for kindness, acceptance and inclusion.

Make it ORANGE and make it end! What are your true colors when it comes to showing that you believe that all youth should be safe from bullying? Come together in one giant ORANGE message of hope and support, WEAR AND SHARE ORANGE to color our nation, and even the world, visibly showing that our society believes that no child should ever experience bullying.

"ORANGE provides a powerful, visually compelling expression of solidarity,‚Äù said Paula Goldberg, Executive Director of PACER Center. ‚ÄúWhether it‚Äôs hundreds of individuals at a school wearing ORANGE, store owners offering ORANGE products, or a community changing a landmark to ORANGE, the vibrant statement becomes a conversation starter, sending the supportive, universal message that bullying is never acceptable behavior.‚Äù"

post_text:
Happy Monday WLA Families!

We wanted to make you aware of an article from Pioneer Press regarding a "dispute" between Woodbury Leadership Academy and the St. Paul Public Schools. Below is our official statement:

"There is no friction between Woodbury Leadership Academy and St. Paul School District. When SPPS purchased the building we were leasing in February of '18, we were thankful that they absorbed our lease and allowed us to finish our 2017-18 school year uninterrupted. After the conclusion of our school year, SPPS understandably became anxious to begin their remodeling efforts. Due to their remodeling efforts during the last month of our lease, SPPS and WLA agreed on a rent reduction. WLA is very complimentary of the way that both organizations worked through the facility transition and wishes SPPS a successful first school year in their new building."

Have a wonderful day!

UPDATE (1): 2nd Grade Field Trip is being rescheduled to April 30th due to the expected rain on April 18th.

Update (2): Due to 4th and 5th grade music rehearsal, we moved the Agricultural Presentation to April 25th. This presentation is for the whole school and student only.

The Agricultural Presentation is hosted by Twin Cities Road Crew. Below is more information from them.

This presentation is interactive, educational, and entertaining. We use our unique platform of music, games, dancing and prizes to deliver an educational message.

We present it in a 45 minute game show style, which encourages kids to participate throughout the assembly.

The programs align with MN State Educational standards!

At the end of each program kids are given an activity bag to take home, with some fun items, pencils, stickers, activity sheets, and more. ALL FREE!!

post_text:
Hello WLA Families!!

Woodbury Leadership Academy will participate in the National Assessment of Educational Progress (NAEP) on February 27th, 2019.

NAEP is the largest nationally representative and continuing assessment of what students know and can do in various subjects. NAEP is administered by the National Center for Education Statistics, within the U.S. Department of Education. NAEP is different from our state assessments because it is a common measure of achievement across the country. The results are released as The Nation‚Äôs Report Card, which provides information about student achievement to educators, parents, policymakers, and the public.

If you have any questions, please contact: Ms. Grubisch at kgrubisch@wlamn.org. She's our District Assessment Coordinator (DAC).

Thank you!

What makes WLA unique? So many things, especially our curriculum! Core Knowledge is content-rich, coherent, cumulative and taught in a content-specific way. The development of Core Knowledge is the result of a lengthy and rigorous process of research. It took into consideration: An international perspective, national reports, state guidelines, subject matter advisors, multicultural advisors and consensus building.

To learn more about Core Knowledge, see the attached image.

WE LOVE CORE KNOWLEDGE!

WE DID IT!! Together, we reached our goal! Thank you for sharing your hard earned dollars with us!! Now we can provide field trip funding and purchase education resources for our students. PLUS we will celebrate with some very fun days - like Crazy Sock Day, PJ Day, Rainbow Day and Decades Day!

Thank you again to all those that contributed and shared with friends+family! We'll be sure to post all our fun from Give to the Max as we have those fun days, go on field trips and use the educational resources!

Have a great FRIDAY! We sure will!!
Friendly reminder: Today is Pizza Friday and Free Dress Friday!
